'''Perfect rhyme''', also called, full rhyme, exact rhyme<ref>http://www.poeticbyway.com/gl-e.html#exact_rhyme</ref>, and true rhyme, is when the later part of the word or phrase is identical sounding to another.<ref>http://www.bartleby.com/61/83/P0188300.html</ref>

For example:

:As the days go '''by'''
:I cannot help but '''sigh'''

Example 2:

Look up into the sky
Boy it is mighty high

